Hey, thanks for checking out this little thing, and yes, the Anderson in the article is related to Anderson robotics.

Credit to Meserach for their idea generator and totallynotspiders who got a similar concept through the generator.



An article about some geese made of machinery that threaten you with the unknown. The article should explore abandonment. So mechanical geese that just seem threatening for no apparent reason…and those exposed to them feel a severe sense of abandonment. As if everything they've ever cared about has left them. Hmmm…
附加记录：    

This is an adaptation of this concept, which from my understanding, has not been adapted to the site yet. Regardless, I'm crediting totallynotspiders for idea inspiration, as well as credit as a co-author.

Image is in the public domain.





